## Page Structure (App Router)

Pages should be thin — they compose components, not contain logic:

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Thin page file
import ItemGrid from '@/components/ItemGrid'
import Footer from '@/components/Footer'
import { PROJECTS_CONTENT } from '@/content/projects'

export default function ProjectsPage() {
  return (
    <main className="min-h-screen">
      <ItemGrid items={PROJECTS_CONTENT.PROJECTS} sectionId="projects" />
      <Footer />
    </main>
  )
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ Bad: Logic in page file
export default function ProjectsPage() {
  const [state, setState] = useState(...)
  // ... lots of JSX and logic
}
```

---

## Reusable Components

When creating display components, make them accept data as props:

```tsx
// ✅ Reusable: Accepts items as prop
interface ItemGridProps {
  items: readonly GridItem[];
  sectionId?: string;
}

export default function ItemGrid({ items, sectionId }: ItemGridProps) {
  // ...
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ Not reusable: Imports data directly
import { PROJECTS_CONTENT } from '@/content/projects'

export default function ItemGrid() {
  // Hardcoded to only work with projects
}
```

