## Types

### Generic Types
Use generic types for reusable components:

```typescript
// types/types.ts
export interface GridItem {
  id: number;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  image?: string;           // Optional fields for flexibility
  technologies?: string[];
  link?: string;
}
```

---

## Asset Naming Conventions

### Images
- Use **kebab-case**: `smart-closet.jpg`, `family-cookbook.jpg`
- Organize in folders: `/projects/`, `/home-carousel/`, `/resume/`
- Use descriptive names, not generic (`cursor-icon.png` not `image.png`)

### Folder Structure
```
public/
  cursor-icon.png           # Site-wide icon
  home-carousel/            # Carousel images
  projects/                 # Project thumbnails
  resume/                   # Resume files
```

---

## Code Hygiene

### Remove Unused Code
- Delete unused components, types, and exports
- Remove unused assets from `public/`
- Don't keep "just in case" code

### Keep Imports Clean
- Only import what you use
- Use path aliases: `@/components/...`, `@/content/...`

