## Adding New Pages

To add a new page (e.g., "Research"):

1. **Create content file**: `content/research.ts`
   ```typescript
   export const RESEARCH_CONTENT = {
     ITEMS: [
       { id: 1, title: '...', description: '...' }
     ]
   } as const;
   ```

2. **Create page**: `app/research/page.tsx`
   ```tsx
   import ItemGrid from '@/components/ItemGrid'
   import { RESEARCH_CONTENT } from '@/content/research'
   
   export default function ResearchPage() {
     return (
       <main>
         <ItemGrid items={RESEARCH_CONTENT.ITEMS} sectionId="research" />
       </main>
     )
   }
   ```

3. **Add to navigation**: `content/navigation.ts`
   ```typescript
   ITEMS: [
     { href: '/', label: 'Home' },
     { href: '/projects', label: 'Projects' },
     { href: '/research', label: 'Research' },  // Add here
     { href: '/resume', label: 'Resume' }
   ]
   ```

---

## Summary

| Need to... | Go to... |
|------------|----------|
| Change text users see | `content/` |
| Change timing/sizes/paths | `constants/config.ts` |
| Add a reusable UI piece | `components/ui/` |
| Add a page section | `components/` |
| Add a new page | `app/` + `content/` |
| Add a shared type | `types/types.ts` |
